/target/
**/target/
Cargo.lock
*.wasm
# Intentional exceptions — these binaries are committed on purpose:
#   - The WASI Preview 1 reactor adapter vendored by `edge build --lang=js`
#     (issue #423; SHA-256 checked by the `rust-js-build` CI job).
#   - The component-model fixtures consumed by edge-worker tests; they were
#     previously `git add -f`-ed in earlier PRs.
!edge-cli/adapters/wasi_snapshot_preview1.reactor.wasm
!edge-worker/tests/fixtures/js_websocket_handler.wasm
!edge-worker/tests/fixtures/handler.wasm
!edge-worker/tests/fixtures/test-handle.wasm
!edge-worker/tests/fixtures/redis_lite.wasm
*.wat
*.log
.env
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.claude/
# Generated by scripts/dev-up.sh on macOS. Overrides /var/edgecloud/registry
# (read-only on macOS) and /usr/local/wasi-sdk/bin defaults. Operators
# regenerate with `make dev-config` after pulling.
edge-control-plane/config.local.yaml
# Artifact-signing keys (issue #307). Operators should NEVER commit
# a generated Ed25519 private key — the wildcard catches hand-named
# files like `signing.key`; the `*.key` form catches suffixes used
# by some secret-management tooling. The pubkey is safe to commit
# but the wildcard covers both, which is the safe default.
*.key
signing.key
